President Muhammadu Buhari has offered his sincere condolences to President Teodoro Obiang Mbasogo of Equatorial Guinea over the explosions at a military base in Bata which wreaked havoc in the city. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that over 30 people have been reported killed with more than 6oo injured in the mishap, which also left homes and buildings in the city with considerable damages. In a condolence message by his spokesman, Malam Garba Shehu, in Abuja on Monday, Buhari extended heartfelt commiserations to those who have lost loved ones in the devastating incident. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! The Nigerian leader also wished those injured speedy recoveries, adding ”the thoughts and prayers of Nigerians are with the people of Equatorial Guinea affected by this tragedy”. (NAN)